  "prompt": "What are the some of the best lines in English songs?",
  "response": "Okay, this is a subjective question, but I'll give you a diverse selection of lines that are widely considered impactful, beautiful, clever, or emotionally resonant, spanning various genres and eras.  I'll try to categorize them a bit to make it easier to browse.\n\n**I. Lines About Love & Relationships:**\n\n*   **\"And in the end, the love you take is equal to the love you make.\" - The Beatles, \"The End\"**:  A simple but profound summation of reciprocal love.\n*   **\"You are the sun, you are the moon, you are the words that I can't say.\" - Florence + The Machine, \"Cosmic Love\"**: Captures the all-encompassing, overwhelming nature of love and its ineffability.\n*   **\"I was scared of dentists and the dark, I was scared of living, I was scared of dying. I had reasons, but now I'm not so sure.\" - The Smiths, \"Asleep\"**: Evokes a fear of the world, but shows a slight shift in perspective.\n*   **\"I know someday you'll have a beautiful life, I know you'll be a star in somebody else's sky, but why, why, why can't it be, can't it be mine?\" - Pearl Jam, \"Black\"**: Captures the pain of unrequited love and letting go.\n*   **\"All you need is love.\" - The Beatles, \"All You Need Is Love\"**: A simple and timeless message about the power of love.\n*   **\"And darling, I will be loving you 'til we're 70. And baby, my heart could still fall as hard at 23.\" - Ed Sheeran, \"Thinking Out Loud\"**: A romantic sentiment about enduring love.\n*   **\"God only knows what I'd be without you.\" - The Beach Boys, \"God Only Knows\"**: Expresses the depth of dependence and gratitude in a relationship.\n*   **\"We found love in a hopeless place.\" - Rihanna, \"We Found Love\"**: Speaks to finding connection and hope in unexpected and difficult circumstances.\n\n**II. Lines About Life, Loss, & Reflection:**\n\n*   **\"And did you get what you wanted from this life, even so? I did.\" - Raymond Carver, \"Late Fragment\" (often set to music)**:  A minimalist yet powerful reflection on satisfaction and acceptance.\n*   **\"The answer, my friend, is blowin' in the wind.\" - Bob Dylan, \"Blowin' in the Wind\"**:  Suggests that the answers to life's big questions are all around us, if we only look and listen.\n*   **\"Nobody said it was easy, no one ever said it would be this hard.\" - Coldplay, \"The Scientist\"**: A relatable expression of the struggles and disappointments of life.\n*   **\"The times they are a-changin'.\" - Bob Dylan, \"The Times They Are A-Changin'\"**: A timeless statement about social and political upheaval.\n*   **\"Hallelujah\" - Leonard Cohen, \"Hallelujah\"**: A word that has taken on a life of its own, conveying a range of emotions from joy to sorrow to resignation.\n*    **\"Holding on to anger is like drinking poison and expecting the other person to die.\" - Unknown (often misattributed to Buddha, but made famous by various songs):** This line is a powerful metaphor for the self-destructive nature of holding onto grudges.\n*   **\"You may say I'm a dreamer, but I'm not the only one. I hope someday you'll join us, and the world will be as one.\" - John Lennon, \"Imagine\"**: A plea for peace and unity.\n*   **\"And it's hard at the end of the day to remember what it was that you set out to do\" - Kate Bush, \"Hounds of Love\"**: Expresses the feeling of being lost and disconnected from one's purpose.\n\n**III. Lines About Identity & Individuality:**\n\n*   **\"I'm just a soul whose intentions are good, oh Lord, please don't let me be misunderstood.\" - Nina Simone, \"Don't Let Me Be Misunderstood\"**: A heartfelt plea for understanding and acceptance.\n*   **\"I'm not afraid to die, I'm afraid of not living.\" - Macklemore & Ryan Lewis, \"Thrift Shop\"**: A raw and honest declaration about facing one's fears.\n*   **\"I'm beautiful in my way, 'cause God makes no mistakes. I'm on the right track, baby, I was born this way.\" - Lady Gaga, \"Born This Way\"**: A powerful anthem of self-acceptance and empowerment.\n*   **\"I will survive.\" - Gloria Gaynor, \"I Will Survive\"**:  A defiant declaration of resilience in the face of adversity.\n*   **\"And I will always love you.\" - Whitney Houston, \"I Will Always Love You\"**: A declaration of unconditional love and acceptance.\n*   **\"I'm a survivor, I'm not gonna give up. I'm gonna work harder, I'm gonna make it.\" - Destiny's Child, \"Survivor\"**: A powerful anthem of resilience and determination.\n\n**IV. Lines with Strong Imagery & Poetic Language:**\n\n*   **\"Tangled up in blue.\" - Bob Dylan, \"Tangled Up in Blue\"**: A vivid and evocative image of emotional turmoil and confusion.\n*   **\"She's got a smile that it seems to me reminds me of childhood memories where everything was as fresh as the bright blue sky.\" - Guns N' Roses, \"Sweet Child o' Mine\"**: A nostalgic and sentimental description of innocence and beauty.\n*   **\"The sky is full of dreams, but you don't know how to fly.\" - Death Cab for Cutie, \"Transatlanticism\"**:  A melancholic line about unfulfilled potential and longing.\n*   **\"Like a rolling stone.\" - Bob Dylan, \"Like a Rolling Stone\"**: Conveys a sense of freedom, but also rootlessness and loss of status.\n*   **\"And the trees are all kept equal by hatchet, axe, and saw.\" - Rush, \"The Trees\"**: A thought-provoking line about forced equality and the suppression of individuality.\n*   **\"You see things much clearer once you're gone.\" - Lorde, \"Ribs\"**:  A nostalgic observation on the fleeting nature of youth and the clarity that comes with distance.\n\n**V. Lines That Are Clever & Witty:**\n\n*   **\"I fought the law, and the law won.\" - The Crickets (covered by The Clash)**:  A self-deprecating and humorous take on rebellion.\n*   **\"It's better to burn out than to fade away.\" - Neil Young (from \"Hey Hey, My My (Into the Black)\"**: A controversial and romanticized view of fame and artistic integrity.\n*   **\"How soon is now?\" - The Smiths, \"How Soon Is Now?\"**: A sarcastic and impatient expression of longing.\n*   **\"We are the champions, my friends, and we'll keep on fighting 'til the end.\" - Queen, \"We Are the Champions\"**: A declaration of victory and resilience.\n*   **\"I'm walking on sunshine, whoa! And don't it feel good!\" - Katrina & The Waves, \"Walking on Sunshine\"**: An upbeat and infectious expression of joy.\n\n**VI. Modern Gems:**\n\n*   **\"I'm only cryptic and Machiavellian 'cause I care.\" - Taylor Swift, \"Mastermind\"**: A self-aware line recognizing the complexities of relationships.\n*   **\"I got new money and it's all cash/ I got new problems and they all crash.\" - Drake, \"Started From the Bottom\"**: Reflects the paradoxical nature of success.\n*   **\"Tell me, what is it you plan to do with your one wild and precious life?\" - Mary Oliver (poet, often quoted in songs)**:  A call to live authentically and with purpose.\n*   **\"Is it over now? Did you forget all about it?\" - Taylor Swift, \"Is It Over Now?\"**: The pain and denial of a broken relationship.\n*  **\"Sometimes, to stay alive, you gotta kill your mind.\" - Twenty One Pilots, \"Migraine\"**: Captures the struggle of coping with mental health challenges.\n\n**To give you the *best* lines, I need a bit more context! Tell me:**\n\n*   **What genres do you like?** (Rock, pop, hip-hop, country, folk, etc.)\n*   **Are you looking for happy lines, sad lines, funny lines, or something else?**\n*   **Are there any artists you particularly enjoy?**\n\nWith a little more information, I can tailor the list to your specific tastes.  Enjoy!\n",
